muros (0.9.16) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Runtime directories: create /var/etc (and the PHP temp/session/cache tree)
    at boot through a systemd-tmpfiles drop-in installed at the path systemd
    actually scans (/usr/lib/tmpfiles.d/muros.conf). On FreeBSD this tree came
    from the mtree /var specification applied by the rc boot scripts, which do
    not run on Debian, so generated service configuration could not be written
    (rename() of dnsmasq hosts/leases and similar files failed with "No such
    file or directory"). The package now also creates the directories during
    install so the first configuration run succeeds without a reboot.
  * util.inc: file_safe() now creates the destination directory before the
    atomic rename, making config writers robust against a missing target path.
  * interfaces.inc: guard hardware-offload settings and IPv6 tracking against a
    minimal configuration (avoid PHP "undefined array key" / "access on null"
    warnings on OPNsense/Interfaces/settings and interfaces.<name>).

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:30:00 +0200

